  "description": "A typography-forward hero where a fixed prefix anchors the headline and a single accent-colored word morphs through a curated sequence — useful for brands that serve multiple verticals or want to demonstrate range in a single line.",
  "descriptions": {
    "descriptive": "Centered, image-free composition: a small eyebrow pill, an oversized two-line headline whose middle slot rotates through up to eight words/phrases (italic, accent-colored, with reserved width to prevent reflow), an optional subheadline, and a primary + secondary CTA pair. Background is a subtle dot grid or horizon-rule motif, both rendered through semantic tokens.",
    "usage": "Best for agencies, platforms, and umbrella brands whose value proposition is multiplicity — 'we serve startups / Fortune 500 / non-profits / governments'. Also strong for category-defining products that want to enumerate the use cases their tool unlocks. Avoid when the headline already has its own punch.",
    "audienceFit": "Reads as confident and current to design-aware buyers — startups, agencies, and creative studios. The rotating slot is a recognized device, so don't lean on it as the surprise; lean on the words themselves being good."
  }
